			<p>Need some help getting up to speed with how our chat system works? Worry not. This page will spin you up faster than a spiral!</p>
			<p>A quite useful feature in Sleepychat is the ability for the chatbar to recognize usernames when you type them, and auto-complete the name for you.
			All you have to do is type the first few letters of their name (at least 2), and you should see a suggestion in the box. Press tab, and if it isn't the
			username you were after, but one similar, just keep pressing tab until you get the right name. Poof! An auto-completed name!</p>
            <p>Here on Sleepychat, you can perform certain actions that normal messages can't perform, by typing any of the following commands and pressing Enter:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>/help -- Launches this page. Duh</li>
                <li>/guide -- Launches a newcomer's guide page.</li>
                <li>/about OR /donate OR /github -- Launches the about page. Duh</li>
                <li>/news -- Re-opens the news ticker if it was closed.</li>
                <li>/ignore &lt;user&gt; -- Ignores all messages for a user.</li>
                <li>/names OR /list -- Toggles the username sidebar on PC, or prints a list of users in the room on mobile.</li>
                <li>/whois &lt;user&gt; -- Display sex and role information for a user.</li>
                <li>/msg &lt;username&gt; &lt;message&gt; -- Sends a private message to the specified user.</li>
                <li>/r OR /reply &lt;message&gt; -- Replies to the last user to privately message you.</li>
                <li>/playground &lt;user&gt; -- Provides a link to The Playground public hypnosis room.</li>
                <li>/room &lt;user&gt; -- Requests a private chat with the specified user.</li>
                <li>/createroom &lt;room name&gt; -- Creates a public room which multiple users can be invited to using\"/invite\".</li>
                <li>/invite &lt;room name&gt; &lt;username1 username2 usernameN&gt; -- Invites the specified user(s) to the specified public room.</li>
                <li>/me &lt;did a thing&gt; -- Styles your message differently to indicate that you're doing an action.</li>
                <li>/coinflip -- Publicly flips a coin.</li>
                <li>/roll &lt;number (optional)&gt; -- Publicly rolls up to 10 dice.</li>
                <li>/clear -- Clears the chat window of all messages.</li>
                <li>/mmsg &lt;message&gt; -- Sends a message to males only.</li>
                <li>/fmsg &lt;message&gt; -- Sends a message to females only.</li>
                <li>/mod &lt;message&gt; -- Sends a message to all moderators online, and the admin.</li>
                <li>/rainy -- I hope you brought your umbrella. (Mobile not supported)</li>
                <li>/lightning -- Definitely not a good time to stand in a clearing. (Mobile not supported)</li>
                <li>/snowy -- ♫ Do you want to build a snowman? ♪. (Seasonal, Mobile not supported)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Also, you can format your messages to be <strong>bold</strong>, <i>italic</i>, or more by using these tricks:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Text surrounded by double dash (--) is <strike>stricken through</strike>.</li>
                <li>Text surrounded by double underscore (__) is <u>underlined</u>.</li>
                <li>Text surrounded by double asterisk (**) is <strong>bolded</strong>.</li>
                <li>Text surrounded by single asterisk (*) is <i>italicized</i>.</li>
                <li>Text surrounded by single grave accents (`) is <span style='font-family: monospace'>monospaced</span>.</li>
                <li>Text surrounded by double grave accents (``) is <span style='font-family: Georgia, serif'>serif font</span>.</li>
            </ul>
